## Rationale
This question evaluates understanding of three-valued constraint propagation with temporal dependencies—a common requirement in streaming policy engines and runtime verification systems.

## Core Concepts
- **Kleene three-valued logic**: Handles uncertainty where partial information exists
- **Online propagation**: Incremental constraint solving as facts arrive per time slice
- **Monotone constraints**: Temporal invariants like P4^{t+1}≤P4^t enforce decreasing behavior

## Propagation Algorithm
```javascript
function propagate(state) {
  let changed = true;
  while (changed) {
    changed = false;
    for (let t = 0; t <= 2; t++) {
      // Implication: (P1∨P2)→P3 becomes ¬(P1∨P2)∨P3
      const antecedent = max(not(state.P1[t]), not(state.P2[t]));
      if (antecedent === T && state.P3[t] === F) {
        state.P3[t] = F; changed = true;
      }
      // Monotonic: P4^{t+1} ≤ P4^t
      if (state.P4[t+1] === T && state.P4[t] === F) {
        state.P4[t+1] = F; changed = true;
      }
      // Cross-slice: ¬P5^t → (P6^{t+1} ∨ P1^t)
      const notP5 = not(state.P5[t]);
      const disjunction = max(state.P6[t+1], state.P1[t]);
      if (notP5 === T && disjunction === F) {
        state.P5[t] = T; changed = true;
      }
    }
  }
  return state;
}
```

